I've successfully implemented the backend test infrastructure for job-service using testcontainers. Here's a summary of what was created:

## Files Created

### 1. `internal/testutil/db.go`
- `SetupPostgresContainer()` - Creates and starts a PostgreSQL container with migrations
- `Cleanup()` - Terminates container and closes connections
- `GetTestDBConnection()` - Returns connection string
- `TruncateAllTables()` - Cleans up data between tests
- `SetupPostgresForTest()` - Convenience function for TestMain

### 2. `internal/testutil/migrate.go`
- `RunMigrations()` - Executes all .up.sql migration files
- `CreateMigrationsTable()` - Tracks applied migrations
- `ExecuteMigrationFile()` - Runs specific migration
- `ExecuteSQL()` - Direct SQL execution
- `ResetMigrations()` - Drops migrations tracking table

### 3. `internal/testutil/fixtures.go`
- `CreateTestOrganization()` - Creates test organization
- `CreateTestUser()` - Creates test user
- `CreateTestAgent()` - Creates test agent
- `CreateTestPrinter()` - Creates test printer
- `CreateTestDocument()` - Creates test document
- `CreateTestPrintJob()` - Creates test print job
- `CreateTestJobAssignment()` - Creates test job assignment
- `CreateTestJobHistory()` - Creates test history entry
- `CreateFullTestSetup()` - Creates complete test data hierarchy
- `SetupTestFixture()` - Returns a TestFixture struct with all entity IDs
- `CleanupTestData()` - Removes all test data

### 4. `internal/testutil/README.md`
- Complete documentation with usage examples
- Function reference table
- Best practices guide

### 5. Updated Test Files
- `job_assignment_test.go` - Uses testcontainers with TestMain, 9+ comprehensive tests
- `job_history_test.go` - Uses testcontainers with TestMain, full CRUD and query tests
- `job_test.go` - Uses testcontainers with TestMain, comprehensive repository tests

### 6. Migration Files
- `migrations/000021_test_setup_functions.up.sql` - Helper functions for tests
- `migrations/000021_test_setup_functions.down.sql` - Rollback migration

### 7. Dependency Update
- Added `github.com/testcontainers/testcontainers-go v0.33.0` to go.mod

All tests are now ready to run with `go test ./services/job-service/repository/...`. The tests will automatically spin up a PostgreSQL container, run migrations, execute tests, and clean up.
